ry 17, 2026)\n- **Votes**: 462 upvotes\n- **Description**: A complete backend service specifically designed for building AI agent applications. Tested on millions of real applications, it's now released as a standalone service, particularly optimized for Claude Code and Cursor.\n- **Key Features**: \n  - Deploy full-stack applications with a single command\n  - No backend setup or configuration needed\n  - AI agents use simple skills instead of complex APIs\n  - Command: `npx base44@latest create`\n- **Keywords**: Backend platform, AI era backend, application building backend, AI agents, full-stack application deployment\n\n### 3. **GitHub Agent HQ** (Launched: February 5-6, 2026)\n- **Votes**: 178-312 upvotes\n- **Tagline**: Use Claude, Codex, and Copilot directly in GitHub and VS Code\n- **Features**: Integration with GitHub agents, Claude, Codex, Copilot, and VS Code\n- **Description**: An AI assistant that provides subscription-based public preview services for developers\n- **Keywords**: GitHub agent, programming assistant, development tools\n\n### 4. **Mastra Code** (Launched: February 27-28, 2026)\n- **Votes**: 204 upvotes\n- **Description**: AI programming agent with observational memory and long-term coding sessions\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Precise context management\n  - Rapid application building\n  - Data compression\n  - Extended coding session support\n- **Keywords**: AI programming agent, observational memory, long-term coding sessions, precise context\n\n### 5. **Orchid 1.0** (Launched: February 25, 2026)\n- **Votes**: 193 upvotes\n- **Description**: An application building tool with AI subscription support\n- **Supported Platforms**: ChatGPT, Claude Code, Gemini, GitHub Copilot\n- **Features**: Free development, API key management, multi-tech stack support\n\n## Industry Trends\n\nThe search results also highlight broader AI product trends from February 2026:\n\n- **Desktop Agent Evolution**: Many AI products are evolving toward desktop-based agents\n- **Integration Focus**: Heavy emphasis on integrating with existing development tools (VS Code, GitHub, Claude)\n- **Code Optimization**: Products specifically designed to optimize Claude Code and Cursor workflows\n- **Backend Simplification**: Tools that remove complexity from backend setup for AI applications\n\nThese launches indicate a strong market trend toward AI-powered coding assistants and agent-based development tools in early 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
