ed how developers were showcasing AI-written projects and their experiences working with AI-generated code.\n\n**2. Notable AI Coding Agent Projects Mentioned:**\n\n- **Prompter Hawk** by nlowell - A task scheduling dashboard for AI agents with features like:\n  - Parallel session monitoring\n  - Cost analysis\n  - Auto-retry functionality\n  - Mermaid architecture diagram generation\n  - The developer mentioned hesitating to post a \"Show HN\" due to poor landing page conversion rates\n\n- **Bambu 3D Printer Client** - A developer spent $65 to have Opus 4.6 create an alternative client for Bambu 3D printers, described as \"zero-cloud, pure offline, cross-VLAN capable\"\n\n**3. Major Trends in February 2026:**\n\n- **Claude Code** celebrating its one-year anniversary with discussions about Agentic AI infrastructure and standardization\n- **Multi-agent orchestration** becoming the main theme of 2026\n- **MCP (Model Context Protocol)** emerging as a standard\n- **Vibe coding** gaining widespread adoption\n- Chinese GLM-5 model launching with strong coding and agent capabilities\n\n**4. Industry Reports:**\n- Peking University released \"Agentic Coding: The Evolution Path from Vibe Coding to Super Individuals\" \n- Anthropic published their \"2026 Agentic Coding Trends Report\"\n- Multiple financial analysts predicting 2026 as the year of agent acceleration\n\n**Note:** The search results primarily come from Chinese tech blogs and news sites discussing Hacker News content, rather than direct links to Hacker News itself. This reflects how AI coding tools and agents had become dominant topics of discussion in developer communities by February 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
