ral Claude Code-related products launched on Product Hunt in February 2026:\n\n- **Happycapy** (Feb 23, 2026) - Top 1 Product Hunt weekly winner\n  - Described as \"a Claude Code computer built into the browser\"\n  - Provides zero-barrier cloud-based agent workstation with pre-installed Claude Code\n  - GUI-based agent environment with file management, terminal, and visualized agent actions\n\n- **Agent Bar** \n  - Runs Claude Code from the macOS menu bar\n  - Provides native GUI for voice interaction, tool call monitoring, and cost tracking\n\n- **Usagebar** (Feb 2026)\n  - macOS menu bar app to track Claude Code usage limits\n  - Monitors the 5-hour and weekly usage caps\n\n### 3. **Ecosystem Products**\n- **Inspector** - \"Figma for Claude Code\" - lets designers edit production websites and apply changes through Claude Code\n- **Vicoa** - Cross-device Claude Code CLI tool with mobile notifications\n- Various macOS GUI tools for easier Claude Code CLI installation and management\n\n### 4. **Industry Context**\nAndrej Karpathy emphasized in late February 2026 that CLI tools are exciting because AI agents can natively use them, compose them together, and interact through the complete terminal toolchain - positioning Claude Code as part of the broader \"build for agents\" movement in 2026.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any of these products or launches?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
